# Backend Python Standards

## Structure
- Routers in `backend/app/routers/`; business logic in `backend/app/services/`
- Config via `backend/app/config.py` (Pydantic Settings from env)
- All API routes under `/api/*`

## Code Quality
- Type hints on all functions
- Pydantic models for request/response bodies; no bare `dict` from API layer
- HTTPException with appropriate status codes; no raw stack traces to clients

## Security
- Secrets only in env vars (see `.env.example`); never commit `.env`
- Validate and sanitize all user input via Pydantic
- Restrict CORS to known dev origins locally; tighten in production

## Efficiency
- Avoid blocking I/O in async handlers without `run_in_executor`
- Do not load large payloads into memory when streaming suffices
- Keep dependencies minimal

## Production
- Serve built frontend from `frontend/dist` via StaticFiles
- API routes registered before static mount so `/api/*` takes precedence
